                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@ajeh It&apos;s not rhetoric. The question is &quot;why do you have to implement templates in a header?&quot;, so I explained the technical choices the C++ language makes that lead to this requirement. Before I wrote my answer others already provided workarounds that are not full solutions, because there &lt;i&gt;can&apos;t&lt;/i&gt; be a full solution. I felt those answers would be complemented by a fuller discussion of the &quot;why&quot; angle of the question.&lt;/span&gt;

